original: Erlandsson, Henning Valdemar, kyrkoherde, Göteryd, f. 12/7/02 i Älg-hult, Kronob. 1., av Erland Gustafsson o. Ingrid Berggren. G. 33 m. skolkökslär, Elsie Gustafson. Barn: UHa (fosterb.) f. 33, Kristina (fosterb.) 42. — Stud :ex. i Växjö 23, teol. fil. ex. i Lund 26, teol. kand. samt prakt, teol. prov 28, prästv. f. Växjö stift 29. Tjg. s. past:adj. i Göteryd o. v. kom-min. i Tutaryd, kommin. i Tutaryd 31, i Älghult 35, kyrkoh. i Göteryd sed. 41.
translated: Erlandsson, Henning Valdemar, a church pastor from Göteryd, born on July 12th, 1902 in Älg-hult, Kronob. His parents were Erland Gustafsson and Ingrid Berggren. He married a school home economics teacher, Elsie Gustafson, in 1933, and they had two foster children: UHa, born in 1933, and Kristina, born in 1942. He studied in Växjö, passing his exam in 1923, and later earned a degree in theology and practical theology from Lund University in 1926 and 1928 respectively. He was ordained as a priest in the Växjö diocese in 1929 and became an assistant pastor in Göteryd and a minister in Tutaryd. He served as a minister in Tutaryd from 1931 to 1935 and in Älghult from 1935 to 1941, when he became a church pastor in Göteryd.
